[[Image:NYC Health and Hospital Police Patch.jpg|thumb|right|200px|<center>A NYC Health and Hospital Police patch]]

The '''New York City Department of Health and Hospitals Police''' is a [[law enforcement agency]] in [[New York City]] thats duties are to provide police services to hospitals operated by the [[New York City Health and Hospitals Corporation]]. 

== History ==

The New York City Health and Hospitals Corporation (HHC) was established in 1970 to operate New York City public hospitals. Until 1973, HHC operated hospitals were patrolled by police officers of the [[New York City Police Department]]. In 1973, Special Patrolman were hired to replace the NYPD officers. But it wasn't until 1980 when <U+201C>special officers employed by the New York City Health and Hospitals Corporation<U+201D> were added to NYS Criminal Procedure Law 2.10, granting the Special Patrolman full peace officer authority.<ref>[http://ypdcrime.com/cpl/article2.htm NYS Criminal Procedure Law Section 2.10 Persons designated as peace officers]</ref>

== About the Officers ==

Officers of the New York City Department of Health and Hospitals Police are unarmed [[peace officer]]s employed by the New York City Health and Hospitals Corporation. NYC Hospital Police Officers have the civil service title of "Special Officer" and the agency job title of "Hospital Police Officer". 

== Power and Authority ==

NYC Hospital Police officers are [[New York State]] [[peace officers]] authorized to make warrantless arrests, make car stops, issue summonses, and use physical and deadly force.<ref>[http://ypdcrime.com/cpl/article2.htm NYS Criminal Procedure Law Section 2.10 Persons designated as peace officers]</ref> <ref>http://ypdcrime.com/cpl/article2.htm Article 2 Peace Officers Section 2.20 Powers of peace officers</ref>

== Training ==

New York City Hospital Police officers undergo five weeks of peace officer training at [[John Jay College of Criminal Justice]] in New York City followed by annual in-service training.

==Line of Duty Deaths==

Since the establishment of the New York City Department of Health and Hospitals Police, 3 officers have died in the line of duty. <ref>http://www.odmp.org/agency/2756-new-york-city-health-and-hospital-police-department-new-york The Officer Down Memorial Page</ref>

